                    <!-- Detailed Instruction Notes -->
                    <h2 class="section-header text-xl">Detailed Instruction Notes</h2>
                    
                    <!-- Introduction -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Introduction (5 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Begin with a hook statistic on average college costs and student loan debt</li>
                            <li>Ask: "How many of you have thought about how you'll pay for education after high school?"</li>
                            <li>Briefly discuss why this topic is critical for all students, regardless of their post-high school plans</li>
                            <li>Set expectations for the day's learning outcomes</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Key Concepts -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Key Concepts (15 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Present the funding priority pyramid (scholarships/grants → work-study → federal loans → private loans)</li>
                            <li>For each funding source, explain:
                              <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                                <li>Basic eligibility requirements</li>
                                <li>Application process</li>
                                <li>Typical award amounts</li>
                                <li>Repayment obligations (if applicable)</li>
                              </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>Use visual comparisons to highlight differences between each option</li>
                            <li>Address common misconceptions, especially about loan obligations and scholarship availability</li>
                            <li>Explain how financial aid packages typically combine multiple funding sources</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- FAFSA Deep Dive -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">The FAFSA Deep Dive (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Explain why the FAFSA is the gateway to most financial aid</li>
                            <li>Walk through key sections using a simplified version</li>
                            <li>Highlight important terminology (EFC, SAR, verification)</li>
                            <li>Discuss deadlines and the importance of early submission</li>
                            <li>Explain dependent vs. independent student status</li>
                            <li>Address privacy concerns students might have about financial information</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Real-World Examples -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Real-World Examples (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Divide class into small groups</li>
                            <li>Assign each group a case study scenario with different student backgrounds</li>
                            <li>Have groups identify the most appropriate funding sources for their scenario</li>
                            <li>Guide groups to consider both immediate costs and long-term implications</li>
                            <li>Facilitate brief presentations of funding recommendations</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Skill Builder Activity -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Skill Builder Activity (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Distribute the mock FAFSA worksheet</li>
                            <li>Guide students through analyzing and completing key sections</li>
                            <li>Focus on interpreting complex questions and required documentation</li>
                            <li>Demonstrate how to use online resources for assistance</li>
                            <li>Provide individual support to students with questions</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Reflection & Wrap-up -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Reflection & Wrap-up (5 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Have students identify which financing options might be most relevant to their personal plans</li>
                            <li>Discuss common challenges in the financial aid process and strategies to overcome them</li>
                            <li>Preview the Day 2 Learning Lab activities</li>
                            <li>Assign any pre-work needed for Day 2</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Discussion Prompts -->
                    <h2 class="section-header text-xl">Discussion Prompts</h2>
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For Introduction:</h3>
                            <p>"How might financing decisions for education impact your financial situation 5-10 years from now?"</p>
                            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Expected responses:</strong> student loan payments affecting housing options, debt-to-income ratio, career choices based on salary potential</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For Key Concepts:</h3>
                            <p>"Why might the funding pyramid prioritize scholarships and grants first?"</p>
                            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Expected responses:</strong> free money, no repayment, reduces overall cost, less financial burden after graduation</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For FAFSA Discussion:</h3>
                            <p>"What circumstances might change a student's financial aid eligibility from year to year?"</p>
                            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Expected responses:</strong> parent income changes, number of family members in college, academic performance</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Differentiation Strategies -->
                    <h2 class="section-header text-xl">Differentiation Strategies</h2>
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For advanced students:</h3>
                        <p>Assign more complex case studies with multiple interacting factors; encourage research on specialized scholarships in their field of interest</p>
                        
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">For struggling students:</h3>
                        <p>Provide a simplified funding options chart; work directly with them on FAFSA terminology; use real examples with clear outcomes</p>
                        
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">For ELL students:</h3>
