                    <!-- Review & Introduction -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Review & Introduction (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Day 1 Concepts to Review:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Funding priority pyramid structure</li>
                            <li>Different types of financial aid</li>
                            <li>FAFSA fundamentals</li>
                            <li>Financial aid packaging</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Podcast Discussion Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>The importance of early planning for financing education</li>
                            <li>Understanding the difference between sticker price and net price</li>
                            <li>The role of education financing in overall financial planning</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Learning Lab Introduction:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Frame today's activities as building on Day 1 conceptual foundation</li>
                            <li>Emphasize the connections between calculator results and actual decision-making</li>
                            <li>Explain that the end product will be a usable education financing plan</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 1 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 1: Education Funding Calculator (12 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Students should access the digital funding calculator</li>
                            <li>Provide sample education costs for different institution types</li>
                            <li>Share estimates for typical financial aid packages</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Demonstrate the calculator with a sample scenario (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students to enter their personalized information (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Allow students to experiment with different scenarios (5 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Facilitate brief sharing of insights and surprises (2 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Focus on the gap between total cost and expected financial aid</li>
                            <li>Emphasize the importance of estimating all costs, not just tuition</li>
                            <li>Discuss strategies for reducing the funding gap</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Check that students are using realistic cost estimates</li>
                            <li>Help students interpret their calculator results</li>
                            <li>Look for students who may need guidance on institutional options</li>
                            <li>Encourage consideration of multiple scenarios</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 2 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 2: Loan Repayment Simulator (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Students should access the loan repayment simulation tool</li>
                            <li>Provide information on current loan interest rates</li>
                            <li>Display a chart of average starting salaries by career field</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Explain how student loan payments impact post-graduation budgets (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Demonstrate how to use the simulator with a sample loan amount (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students to calculate payments based on their funding gap (4 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Facilitate analysis of payment-to-income ratios (2 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>The concept of debt-to-income ratio and its importance</li>
                            <li>How loan terms and interest rates affect total repayment</li>
                            <li>Strategic borrowing aligned with expected future income</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Ensure students understand the long-term implications of different loan amounts</li>
                            <li>Help students connect loan payments to their career path salary expectations</li>
                            <li>Look for unrealistic borrowing projections to address</li>
                            <li>Encourage consideration of various repayment strategies</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 3 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 3: Scholarship Search Strategy (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Provide scholarship search strategy template</li>
                            <li>Share list of scholarship search engines and resources</li>
                            <li>Display examples of scholarship categories</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Review different types of scholarships and their requirements (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students in identifying personal strengths and affiliations (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Support students in developing tailored search approaches (4 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Demonstrate effective application tracking systems (1 minute)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>The importance of volume and persistence in scholarship applications</li>
                            <li>How to match personal attributes to scholarship opportunities</li>
                            <li>Strategies for standing out in scholarship applications</li>
                            <li>Creating a sustainable application schedule</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Ensure students are considering diverse scholarship sources</li>
                            <li>Help students develop realistic scholarship application timelines</li>
                            <li>Encourage specific rather than generic strategy development</li>
                            <li>Look for opportunities to suggest specialized scholarships based on interests</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 4 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 4: Financing Plan Creation (8 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Provide comprehensive education financing plan template</li>
                            <li>Display model example of a completed plan</li>
                            <li>Arrange for individual work with teacher circulation</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Explain the components of a complete financing plan (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students in integrating findings from previous activities (1 minute)</li>
                            <li>Support students in creating action steps and timelines (4 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Check for plan completeness and feasibility (1 minute)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Creating a financing strategy is an iterative process</li>
                            <li>The importance of backup options and contingency planning</li>
                            <li>How to create specific, actionable next steps</li>
                            <li>Aligning financing plans with career and educational goals</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Check for alignment between educational aspirations and financial reality</li>
                            <li>Help students identify specific action steps with deadlines</li>
                            <li>Look for gaps in planning that need to be addressed</li>
                            <li>Encourage thinking about both short-term and long-term steps</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Reflection & Wrap-up -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Reflection & Wrap-up (5 minutes)</h3>
